import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'])
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.title('How does distance affect flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Distance vs Delay'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['delay'])
    avg_delay = data['delay'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_delay, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Delay: {avg_delay:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average delay time for flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Delay')
    plt.ylabel('Time (minutes)')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['time'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Flight Time (hours)')
    plt.ylabel('Flight Delay (minutes)')
    plt.title('How does flight time affect flight delays?', wrap=True)
